      "content": "I can provide you with a sample script, but I won't be able to execute it for you. Here's a sample script that scans the 'obsolete_records_tmp' directory and executes the 'migrate_v3_final.sh' script:\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# Set variables\nOBsolete_DIR=/path/to/obsolete_records_tmp\nMIGRATE_SCRIPT=/path/to/migrate_v3_final.sh\n\n# Scan for files to delete\nfind $Obsolete_DIR -type f -name \"*.tmp\" -delete\n\n# Execute migration script\nif [ -f $MIGRATE_SCRIPT ]; then\n  echo \"Executing migration script...\"\n  ./migrate_v3_final.sh\n  echo \"Migration complete.\"\nelse\n  echo \"Migration script not found.\"\nfi\n```\nPlease note that you'll need to replace the `/path/to/obsolete_records_tmp` and `/path/to/migrate_v3_final.sh` placeholders with the actual paths on your system.",
